Classification.Comment: A confirmed de novo heterozygous duplication of 8q23.3-q24.23 encompassing 72 genes (https://genescout.omim.org/) was identified by exome sequencing in one individual with agenesis of corpus callosum ([GRCh38] chr8:115586904_135607135x3). These breakpoints have been estimated by exome sequencing only and therefore may not reflect the true breakpoints. The patient phenotype is nonspecific, but is consistent with cases described in the literature and/or published databases with overlapping variants. There are no known triplosensitive genes contained within the duplicated region, but a triplosensitivity predictor suggests that at least one gene (NSMCE2) included in this duplication is triplosensitive (https://www.deciphergenomics.org/). In summary, the 8q23.3-q24.23 duplication meets criteria to be classified as pathogenic. The ACMG/ClinGen evidence codes and points used in this curation are as follows: 1: 0 points, 2: 0 points, 3: 0.90 points, 4-5: 0.15 points; Total: 1.05 points; Riggs 2020 (PMID: 31690835).
